article.description: — Robert Braswell's 21 points helped Charlotte defeat Greensboro College 91-44 on Friday.
article.headline: Braswell's 21 help Charlotte defeat Greensboro College 91-44
article.linkText: Braswell's 21 help Charlotte defeat Greensboro College 91-44
article.story: CHARLOTTE, N.C. -- — Robert Braswell's 21 points helped Charlotte defeat Greensboro College 91-44 on Friday. Braswell also had nine rebounds for the 49ers (6-5). Jackson Threadgill scored 14 points and added four steals. Isaiah Folkes had 11 points and finished 5 of 7 from the floor. The Pride were led by Matthew Brown, who recorded 12 points. Erik Alvey added eight points for Greensboro. In addition, Isaiah Pruett had eight points and six assists. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
